RACE.RACE_TEXT: MONMOUTH PARK RACE 3 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 22100. (PLUS UP TO 40% NJB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE DECEMBER 9 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VOICE OF SPRING raced four wide into the first turn, rated the pace racing on the outside, dueled between rivals on the far turn, led into the stretch, then dueled with SHEA ON A MISSION through the final furlong and prevailed. SHEA ON A MISSION vied inside for the early lead, then stalked the pace, bid three wide entering the far turn, dueled outside rivals, then dueled with the winner in the stretch run and dug in gamely outside to the finish. CANOOCHEE was off slowly, tracked on the inside, made a rail bid, dueled inside rivals on the far turn, steadied in tight behind VOICE OF SPRING at the top of the stretch, then weakened and held for third. NANA FANNY stumbled at the start, stalked three wide, chased the leaders on the far turn, lacked a bid and tired. MANI PEDI raced off the pace inside, failed to threaten, then steadied when in tight between rivals at the sixteenth pole. BOURN WILD AGAIN raced three wide early, then two wide off the pace and gave way. After reviewing Jockey Objections by, CANOOCHEE against the winner and MANI PEDI against NANA FANNY, the race was declared official.
